Police are investigating the death of a couple on Durban's beachfront. The bodies were discovered by a passer-by. eNCA reporter Dasen Thathiah reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The two people whose bodies were found on a Durban beach have been identified. Fathima Muhammad, (50), of Chatsworth and Kresen Chandiah, (24), were discovered by a passer-by who was collecting pieces of scrap paper and bottles. READ: Rape suspect linked to Hess double murder Muhammad, a mother of three children, was last seen Monday on her way to Suncoast for lunch. Chandiah's family says that he worked as a tiler.